parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring perch can cause the front suspension to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Loud bang or snapping noise
front end of the vehicle drops
loss of steering control
vehicle leans to one side
front coil spring protrudes from the perch
rust or corrosion on the spring perch or welds.

symptoms: The vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting
the check engine light is illuminated
the airbag light is illuminated
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
the wires in the harness are brittle
cracked
or corroded
the insulation on the wires is deteriorated
and the wires are shorting or burning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents, strand the driver, and cause inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting
the starter motor is faulty
the starter motor is worn out
and the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents, strand the driver, and cause inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting

the ignition switch is worn out
and the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the safety restraint system can render the airbags and other safety features useless, increasing the risk of injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.

safety equipment is rendered useless
